nba_1` (Warriors vs. Lakers) included odds from \"Hard Rock Bet\" and \"CBS Sports.\"\n","    *   NFL game `nfl_1` (Chiefs vs. Bills) included odds from \"Hard Rock Bet\" and \"ESPN Bet.\"\n","*   \"Hard Rock Bet\" was consistently represented as a data source across all three sports (MLB, NBA, NFL) in the mock data, fulfilling the requirement for its inclusion.\n","*   Each odds entry maintained a consistent structure, including `game_id`, `home_team`, `away_team`, `source`, `money_line_home`, and `money_line_away`, which is crucial for subsequent data processing and comparison.\n","*   A conceptual data validation mechanism was proposed, outlining detailed steps for cross-validation and reconciliation of lineup information (teams, game times, player names) to ensure accuracy and consistency across diverse data sources.\n","\n","### Insights or Next Steps\n","*   The current mock `AuthenticOddsScraper` successfully demonstrates multi-source data integration; however, implementing real-world scraping logic for Hard Rock, CBS, ESPN, and other sports outlets would be the next critical step to gather live, dynamic odds.\n","*   Develop a concrete implementation of the proposed data validation mechanism, focusing initially on team name normalization and game time standardization, to ensure data consistency before feeding into any prediction models. This should include defining priority rules and alert systems for discrepancies.\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"1c562802"},"source":["# Task\n","Summarize how the system integrates diverse sports data sources from Hard Rock, CBS, and ESPN, and how mechanisms for ensuring lineup accuracy (teams, game times, player names) can be implemented."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"6e6b1b39"},"source":["## Analyze Captured Odds Data\n","\n","### Subtask:\n","Parse the output from `show_sportsbook_odds` to verify that data from various sources (including Hard Rock) is present and correctly structured for ensu