 the home team is favored by 5.5 points.\n","5. Compare the spreads and their associated odds across different sources for the same game to highlight any discrepancies or commonalities.\n","6. For each game, summarize the market consensus on the point spread and the expected winning margins, if available from multiple sources.\n","7. Add a new field, for example, `implied_spread_outcome` to each odds entry, indicating which team is expected to cover the spread based on the spread value (e.g., 'Home team covers', 'Away team covers', or 'Push' if spread is an integer and teams tie by that margin)."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"60de5fb9"},"source":["## Integrate with External Prediction Factors\n","\n","### Subtask:\n","Combine the aggregated NBA odds data with external prediction factors, specifically team form, to refine implied probabilities.\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"69da65df"},"source":["**Reasoning**:\n","The subtask requires defining the `TeamFormPlugin` class with specific mock form data for the relevant NBA teams and then applying its logic to adjust probabilities in the `nba_game_details_data`. I will define the class in this step.\n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"ac2ffb75","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773355726294,"user_tz":240,"elapsed":49,"user":{"displayName":"garry evans","userId":"18049878967172356456"}},"outputId":"fa7966a6-0dcc-4146-d20b-6ac5c63abd1e"},"source":["class TeamFormPlugin:\n","    def __init__(self):\n","        self.team_forms = {\n","            \"Sixers\": {\"team\": \"Sixers\", \"form\": [1, 1, 0, 1, 1]}, # W W L W W\n","            \"Pistons\": {\"team\": \"Pistons\", \"form\": [0, 0, 1, 0, 0]}, # L L W L L\n","            \"Suns\": {\"team\": \"Suns\", \"form\": [1, 1, 1, 1, 0]}, # W W W W L\n","            \"Pacers\": {\"team\": \"Pacers\", \"form\": [0, 0, 0, 0, 1]}, # L L L L W\n","            \"Wizards\": {\"team\": \"Wizards\", \"form\": [0, 0, 0, 0, 0]}, # L L L L L\n","            \"Magic\": {\"team\": \"Magic\", \"form\": [1, 1, 1, 1, 1]}, # W W W W W\n","            \"Nets\": {\"team\": \"Nets\", \"form\": [0, 1, 0, 1, 0]}, # L W L W L\n","            \"Hawks\": {\"team\": \"Hawks\", \"form\": [1, 0, 1, 0, 1]} # W L W L W\n","        }\n","\n","    def get_form_data(self, team_name):\n","        # Return specific form data or a default if not found\n","        return self.team_forms.get(team_name, {\"team\": team_name, \"form\": [0, 0, 0, 0, 0]}) # Default to no wins\n","\n","print(\"TeamFormPlugin class defined with mock NBA team form data.\")"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["TeamFormPlugin class defined with mock NBA team form data.\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"f8521375"},"source":["**Reasoning**:\n","The `TeamFormPlugin` class has been defined. Now, I will instantiate it and apply its logic to adjust the `true_prob_home` and `true_prob_away` values in the `nba_game_details_data` based on team form, as per the subtask instructions. This involves iterating through games, calculating form scores, adjusting probabilities, and adding `form_notes`.\n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"d1a5b716","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773355748962,"user_tz":240,"elapsed":66,"user":{"displayName":"garry evans","userId":"18049878967172356456"}},"outputId":"543d0b75-a2fb-45db-d522-37e6b3f7d192"},"source":["import json\n","\n","# Assuming nba_game_details_data is already loaded and updated with true probabilities\n","# Assuming TeamFormPlugin class is defined in the previous step\n","\n","team_form_plugin = TeamFormPlugin()\n","\n","adjustment_percentage = 0.02 # 2% adjustment\n","\n","for game_key, game_data in nba_game_details_data.items():\n","    for odds_entry in game_data['odds']:\n","        home_team = odds_entry['home_team']\n","        away_team = odds_entry['away_team']\n","\n","        home_form_data = team_form_plugin.get_form_data(home_team)\n","        away_form_data = team_form_plugin.get_form_data(away_team)\n","\n","        home_form_score = sum(home_form_data['form'])\n","        away_form_score = sum(away_form_data['form'])\n","\n","        form_adjusted_true_prob_home = odds_entry['true_prob_home']\n","        form_adjusted_true_prob_away = odds_entry['true_prob_away']\n","        form_notes = \"No form adjustment.\"\n","\n","        # Determine which team is favored by money line (or has higher true probability)\n","        if odds_entry['true_prob_home'] > odds_entry['true_prob_away']:\n","            favored_prob = odds_entry['true_prob_home']\n","            underdog_prob = odds_entry['true_prob_away']\n","            favored_team_ml = home_team\n","            underdog_team_ml = away_team\n","        else:\n","            favored_prob = odds_entry['true_prob_away']\n","            underdog_prob = odds_entry['true_prob_home']\n","            favored_team_ml = away_team\n","            underdog_team_ml = home_team\n","\n","        if home_form_score > away_form_score:\n","            # Home team has better form, increase favored team's probability if home is favored\n","            # Or increase home team's probability if it's the underdog in ML terms\n","            if favored_team_ml == home_team:\n","                form_adjusted_true_prob_home = round(min(1.0, odds_entry['true_prob_home'] * (1 + adjustment_percentage)), 4)\n","                # Adjust away prob proportionally to keep sum close to 1, or just scale down\n","                form_adjusted_true_prob_away = round(max(0.0, odds_entry['true_prob_away'] * (1 - adjustment_percentage)), 4)\n","                form_notes = f\"Confidence in {home_team} increased by {adjustment_percentage*100:.0f}% due to better home team form.\"\n","            else:\n","                # If away is favored by ML, but home has better form, slight bump to home prob\n","                form_adjusted_true_prob_home = round(min(1.0, odds_entry['true_prob_home'] * (1 + adjustment_percentage/2)), 4)\n","                form_adjusted_true_prob_away = round(max(0.0, odds_entry['true_prob_away'] * (1 - adjustment_percentage/2)), 4)\n","                form_notes = f\"Slight confidence adjustment for {home_team} (+{adjustment_percentage*50:.0f}%) due to better home team form despite being ML underdog.\"\n","\n","        elif away_form_score > home_form_score:\n","            # Away team has better form, increase favored team's probability if away is favored\n","            # Or increase away team's probability if it's the underdog in ML terms\n","            if favored_team_ml == away_team:\n","                form_adjusted_true_prob_away = round(min(1.0, odds_entry['true_prob_away'] * (1 + adjustment_percentage)), 4)\n","                form_adjusted_true_prob_home = round(max(0.0, odds_entry['true_prob_home'] * (1 - adjustment_percentage)), 4)\n","                form_notes = f\"Confidence in {away_team} increased by {adjustment_percentage*100:.0f}% due to better away team form.\"\n","            else:\n","                # If home is favored by ML, but away has better form, slight bump to away prob\n","                form_adjusted_true_prob_away = round(min(1.0, odds_entry['true_prob_away'] * (1 + adjustment_percentage/2)), 4)\n","                form_adjusted_true_prob_home = round(max(0.0, odds_entry['true_prob_home'] * (1 - adjustment_percentage/2)), 4)\n","                form_notes = f\"Slight confidence adjustment for {away_team} (+{adjustment_percentage*50:.0f}%) due to better away team form despite being ML underdog.\"\n","\n","        # Ensure probabilities sum to roughly 1 after adjustment, and are within [0,1]\n","        total_adjusted_prob = form_adjusted_true_prob_home + form_adjusted_true_prob_away\n","        if total_adjusted_prob != 0:\n","            form_adjusted_true_prob_home = round(form_adjusted_true_prob_home / total_adjusted_prob, 4)\n","            form_adjusted_true_prob_away = round(form_adjusted_true_prob_away / total_adjusted_prob, 4)\n","\n","        odds_entry['form_adjusted_true_prob_home'] = form_adjusted_true_prob_home\n","        odds_entry['form_adjusted_true_prob_away'] = form_adjusted_true_prob_away\n","        odds_entry['form_notes'] = form_notes\n","\n","print(\"Calculated and adjusted probabilities based on team form.\")\n","\n","# Print a sample of the updated nba_game_details_data to verify\n","print(\"\\n--- Sample of NBA Game Details with Form-Adjusted Probabilities ---\")\n","# Limiting output to the first game for brevity\n","for game_key, game_data in nba_game_details_data.items():\n","    print(f\"Game: {game_key}\")\n","    for entry in game_data['odds']:\n","        print(f\"  Source: {entry['source']}\")\n","        print(f\"    Original True Prob Home: {entry['true_prob_home']}\")\n","        print(f\"    Original True Prob Away: {entry['true_prob_away']}\")\n","        print(f\"    Form Adjusted True Prob Home: {entry['form_adjusted_true_prob_home']}\")\n","        print(f\"    Form Adjusted True Prob Away: {entry['form_adjusted_true_prob_away']}\")\n","        print(f\"    Form Notes: {entry['form_notes']}\")\n","    break # Only print the first game for sample"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Calculated and adjusted probabilities based on team form.\n","\n","--- Sample of NBA Game Details with Form-Adjusted Probabilities ---\n","Game: Sixers @ Pistons\n","  Source: Hard Rock Bet\n","    Original True Prob Home: 0.6164\n","    Original True Prob Away: 0.3836\n","    Form Adjusted True Prob Home: 0.6117\n","    Form Adjusted True Prob Away: 0.3883\n","    Form Notes: Slight confidence adjustment for Sixers (+1%) due to better away team form despite being ML underdog.\n","  Source: CBS Sports\n","    Original True Prob Home: 0.6092\n","    Original True Prob Away: 0.3908\n","    Form Adjusted True Prob Home: 0.6044\n","    Form Adjusted True Prob Away: 0.3956\n","    Form Notes: Slight confidence adjustment for Sixers (+1%) due to better away team form despite being ML underdog.\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"9914af18"},"source":["## Develop a Prediction Algorithm\n","\n","### Subtask:\n","Based on the integrated data, develop or utilize a prediction algorithm (e.g., a machine learning model, a statistical model, or a rule-based system) that outputs a predicted winner, a predicted score, or a predicted probability distribution for outcomes. This algorithm should weigh the influence of market odds against your own analytical factors.\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"aab3c138"},"source":["**Reasoning**:\n","I need to define a Python function `predict_nba_game` that encapsulates the rule-based prediction logic for both money line and spread outcomes, as described in the subtask instructions. This function will be applied to each NBA game to generate predictions.\n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"id":"f103318f"},"source":["def predict_nba_game(game_data: dict) -> dict:\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Generates rule-based predictions for NBA games based on aggregated odds and form-adjusted probabilities.\n","\n","    Args:\n","        game_data (dict): A dictionary containing 'requested_game' and a list of 'odds' entries\n","                          for a single NBA game, including money line and spread information,\n","                          true probabilities, and form-adjusted probabilities.\n","\n","    Returns:\n","        dict: A dictionary containing the predicted winner, win probability, spread outcome,\n","              and spread confidence. Returns None if predictions cannot be made.\n","    \"\"\"\n","    if not game_data or not game_data.get('odds'):\n","        return {\"error\": \"No odds data available for this game.\"}\n","\n","    # Use the first odds entry as a representative for team names and game_id\n","    # In a real system, we would average or pick the most reliable source\n","    representative_odds = game_data['odds'][0]\n","    home_team = representative_odds['home_team']\n","    away_team = representative_odds['away_team']\n","    game_id = representative_odds['game_id']\n","\n","    # --- Money Line Prediction ---\n","    # Aggregate form-adjusted probabilities across sources for robustness\n","    avg_form_adjusted_true_prob_home = sum(e['form_adjusted_true_prob_home'] for e in game_data['odds']) / len(game_data['odds'])\n","    avg_form_adjusted_true_prob_away = sum(e['form_adjusted_true_prob_away'] for e in game_data['odds']) / len(game_data['odds'])\n","\n","    predicted_winner = None\n","    predicted_win_probability = 0.0\n","\n","    if avg_form_adjusted_true_prob_home > avg_form_adjusted_true_prob_away:\n","        predicted_winner = home_team\n","        predicted_win_probability = avg_form_adjusted_true_prob_home\n","    else:\n","        predicted_winner = away_team\n","        predicted_win_probability = avg_form_adjusted_true_prob_away\n","\n","    # --- Spread Prediction ---\n","    predicted_spread_outcome = \"No clear spread prediction\"\n","    predicted_spread_confidence = 0.0\n","\n","    # For spread prediction, let's use the first source's spread as a basis\n","    # In a real system, a more complex aggregation or weighted average might be used\n","    first_spread_home = representative_odds.get('spread_home')\n","    first_spread_away = representative_odds.get('spread_away')\n","\n","    # Get home/away money line odds from the representative_odds for initial favored team check\n","    # It's better to use the already calculated avg_form_adjusted_true_prob for favored team\n","\n","    if first_spread_home is not None and first_spread_away is not None:\n","        # Determine the bookie-favored team based on the spread value (negative spread)\n","        bookie_favored_team = None\n","        if first_spread_home < 0: # Home team is favored by bookie\n","            bookie_favored_team = home_team\n","            spread_value = abs(first_spread_home)\n","        elif first_spread_away < 0: # Away team is favored by bookie\n","            bookie_favored_team = away_team\n","            spread_value = abs(first_spread_away)\n","        else:\n","            # This case means both spreads are positive, which is unusual for a traditional favorite\n","            # For this mock, we'll assume no strong bookie favorite via spread\n","            bookie_favored_team = None\n","\n","        # Rule-based logic for spread prediction\n","        # Condition 1: Our predicted winner aligns with bookie's favored team\n","        # Condition 2: Our confidence in the predicted winner is high (e.g., > 60%)\n","        # Condition 3: The spread is not excessively large (e.g., abs(spread) < 7.0)\n","        # This threshold could be dynamic or learned\n","\n","        if predicted_winner == bookie_favored_team:\n","            if predicted_winner == home_team and avg_form_adjusted_true_prob_home > 0.60 and abs(first_spread_home) < 7.0: # Home is favored and confidence is high and spread is reasonable\n","                predicted_spread_outcome = f\"{home_team} to cover {-abs(first_spread_home)}\"\n","                predicted_spread_confidence = min(1.0, predicted_win_probability + 0.1) # Boost confidence for spread match\n","            elif predicted_winner == away_team and avg_form_adjusted_true_prob_away > 0.60 and abs(first_spread_away) < 7.0: # Away is favored and confidence is high and spread is reasonable\n","                predicted_spread_outcome = f\"{away_team} to cover {-abs(first_spread_away)}\"\n","                predicted_spread_confidence = min(1.0, predicted_win_probability + 0.1)\n","            else:\n","                # If confidence is not high enough or spread is too large, predict underdog covers\n","                predicted_spread_outcome = f\"{(away_team if predicted_winner == home_team else home_team)} to cover {abs(first_spread_away if predicted_winner == home_team else first_spread_home)}\"\n","                predicted_spread_confidence = max(0.1, predicted_win_probability - 0.1)\n","        else: # Our predicted winner is the underdog according to bookie spread\n","            # If our predicted winner is the underdog, we predict them to cover the spread\n","            # The confidence might be adjusted downwards, as we are going against bookie spread's favorite\n","            if predicted_winner == home_team: # Our home predicted winner is bookie's underdog\n","                predicted_spread_outcome = f\"{home_team} to cover {abs(first_spread_home)}\"\n","                predicted_spread_confidence = max(0.1, predicted_win_probability - 0.05)\n","            elif predicted_winner == away_team: # Our away predicted winner is bookie's underdog\n","                predicted_spread_outcome = f\"{away_team} to cover {abs(first_spread_away)}\"\n","                predicted_spread_confidence = max(0.1, predicted_win_probability - 0.05)\n","\n","    return {\n","        \"game_id\": game_id,\n","        \"predicted_winner\": predicted_winner,\n","        \"predicted_win_probability\": round(predicted_win_probability, 4),\n","        \"predicted_spread_outcome\": predicted_spread_outcome,\n","        \"predicted_spread_confidence\": round(predicted_spread_confidence, 4)\n","    }"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"a937fd7a"},"source":["**Reasoning**:\n","The `predict_nba_game` function has been defined. Now, I will apply this function to each game in the `nba_game_details_data` dictionary to generate money line and spread predictions and store them in a new 'predictions' key within each game's data.\n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"acf798ad","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773355806507,"user_tz":240